Basically it's officially Summer, and I'm in love with it. Last weekend I went camping and Shannon came even though it was all last minute. It was pretty much amazing and we are obsessed with boat. Haha yeah but she's close and by the end of the summer she will be a perfectionist. By the way Shannon and I like to be destructive and break things on the pavement. =)

Anyways, we got home yesterday and I went for a run. It felt good to run but I'm so incrediably out of shape, so I think I'm going to run everyday now. Today I woke up and went on the computer as usual. Then I vacuumed the pool. Oh yes, and I would like to say that skimming the pool is an art form and I'm addicted to it. Haha I'm weird and I know it.

Oh yeah and conversations with my sister last night made me happy. And conversations with Kelly were good too. I like operation blue bananas even though I find it near impossible. Yes only Kelly knows operation blue bananas. Haha we are weird and we know it. =)

Okay so I will spend the rest of the day outside in the pool by myself because I have no friends and what not. Oh yeah and I have zero plans for this week. I'm cool. I think that Shannon, me, Kelly, and Emily need to hang out this week sometime if that's cool with them because we are all so hot. Honostly though, Shannon is in love with Emily and Kelly and thinks they are amazing which makes me happy.

I <3 Summer! Awesome! =D

Today was sunday and I had an excellent day I must admit. First I got up and cleaned my room which wasn't that fun but it only took an hour and I love clean rooms. Then Kelly, Milane, and Jillian came over and it was awesome. I kind of had like a lot of fun and I really like our new sport with the volleyball and the baseball bat. Yeah, so we taped and stuff and it was super hot but we got through it with ice cream and pickles. We took sweet pictures and we looked sexy in them. Then I was debating on whether or not to go to Steph's because I have like beyond imagination amounts of homework. But I ended up going and it was pretty much freaking amazing. I love to laugh. Love it love it love it love it. Kim is kind of awesome and we are the most amazing tigers that hiss ever. And Shannon is life as usual because we are cool and beat eachother up. I kind of punched her in the throat but she deserved it because she attacked me. Yes and I hope Steph had a freaking amazing birthday because she deserves it a lot. 

Well now I'm home and I have to take a shower and do homework...ahhh! Honostly though, today is the first day in the longest time I can truely say that I had a good day. Everything was just perfect. It's like nothing bad ever existed and everyone was just happy to be with eachother. I wish everyday could be like today was. I feel happy today and it's maybe the best feeling ever. I think I've almost forgotten what it feels like to be truely happy. It mind sound dumb but it's so true. I am determined to make things happen like this more often. Good days.

I have a friend. Just one. And her name is SHANNON and she freaking equals LIFE! We went to see the Sisterhood of the traveling pants and then went back to her house and watched the Moulin Rouge last night. Then I slept over and she made me breakfast in the morning because she is love. It was so fun because she it hottttttt and I'm obsessed with her. We talk about how the same exact things have happened to us with our friends and wonder if it was all becuase club volleyball took up so much time. I just really love her to death though, and she saves me from being friendless. Basically, she is all I have right now and it's hard. As amazing as this girl is and how much I say I love her because I do, it's important to say that my old friends can never be replaced. I miss them so much...so much. I guess I'm just trying to make the best of moving on, but it's just hard because I'm constantly thinking about what my old friends are doing together at every moment and if they EVER think about me or miss me. For some reason though it seems that they have moved on way to easily and I have been replaced by better things, and nobody knows what it feels like to be forgotten about by you're best friends unless its happened to them. Even if I never go back to being friends with the people I love the most, I will never forget everything we experienced together. Nobody I ever meet will be able to take the place of these girls and no memory will ever come close to being as amazing as the ones made with them. Maybe the reason I want all of my friends to know that they will never be replaced is because if by any slim chance they still care, I never want them to feel how I feel everyday of my life.

Last weekend was Penn State and it was amazing with my freaking awesome volleyball girls. I love them so much and they showed me that there are so much better things out there for me just by being the freaking amazingest people ever. The whole thing with the coach and my parents was kind of ugly but you know what, its over and it still was a freaking sweet weekend with the girls. I seriously have never laughed  as hard as I was on the way home with Kim and Sam. It was freaking insane and we like red trucks and trees. Haha wow I love them. It was really wierd because I was totally out of control and being like insanly crazy with the entire team this weekend and it made me think back to old times with friends. I wonder why I stopped acting like that and being myself (all crazy) around them. Sometimes I think its just because I feel out of place, but really I don't know...things just changed. Ew for change I miss old times. 

When I got home and read an entry in this one journal it really upset me. I know that one sentence was about me but it basically was like oh well things happen too bad and brushed it off. I guess they are over me and don't want to even be close anymore but whatever because I've clearly been replaced by way better people than I ever could be so it's all good. Not really but we will pretend, and its the absolute truth...we will pretend everything is good but things will never get better or go back. I no longer have you to call my best friend. I no longer know who you are. We will never talk about the things we talked about before. We will never do the crazy things we once did. We won't spend summer nights just being crazy girls or laugh together and not need someone else to be there. Things are never going back as much as I would do to make them. What really makes me get upset is thinking back to this one time that I asked you, "Do you think we will be best friends forever" and you told me that you deffintly thought that we would always be best friends no matter what. And then I told you that I thought that I didn't think we would because I knew something like this would happen. The worst got the best of us and it's over just like that. You've clearly moved on, unfortunatly for me it takes more time than this, but I will...eventually...someday...hopefully. I'm just sorry about the way things had to end and mostly I'm sorry because I miss you.

I will be the best me that I can.  I know I have so much potential and I have been squandering it away frivolously. Every minute that I allow to pass by with out moving myself forward is wasted youth.  I am committed to letting the trapped me come out and shine."
